# Cursor Rules for iouthna

## Learning Preferences

### Visual Learning Style
- **Primary Learning Method**: Visual learner - learns better with diagrams and visual representations
- **Preference**: When creating documentation, guides, or explaining concepts, always include:
  - Process flow diagrams (using Mermaid)
  - Architecture diagrams
  - Sequence diagrams
  - Data flow diagrams
  - Entity relationship diagrams
  - Workflow diagrams
  - Hierarchy diagrams
  - Visual examples and illustrations

### Documentation Standards
- Always add visual diagrams to documentation to enhance understanding
- Use Mermaid diagrams for technical documentation
- Place diagrams in relevant sections to support visual learning
- Include multiple diagram types when explaining complex concepts
- Diagrams should be clear, well-labeled, and connected to text explanations

### Example Implementation
- When creating guides or documentation, follow the pattern established in SAP-Guides:
  - Add diagrams after section introductions
  - Include process flows for business processes
  - Add architecture diagrams for system designs
  - Use sequence diagrams for interactions
  - Include ER diagrams for data models
  - Add workflow diagrams for approval processes

## General Preferences
- Prefer comprehensive, detailed documentation
- Include practical examples in documentation
- Use structured formats (tables, lists, diagrams)
- Maintain consistency across documentation

